THOUGHT: The crash occurs because GVN attempts to split a critical edge where the terminator is an IndirectBrInst, which BreakCriticalEdges explicitly disallows. I will locate GVN.cpp and modify splitCriticalEdges to skip splitting when either the source terminator is an IndirectBrInst or the destination has an IndirectBr predecessor. Then I will run submit-patch to verify.

```bash
nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp | sed -n '3120,3185p' && \
python3 - <<'PY'
import re,sys
path='llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp'
with open(path,'r') as f: s=f.read()
orig=s
# Insert guard into splitCriticalEdges to avoid IndirectBrInst sources/dests
pattern=r'(BasicBlock\*\s+GVNPass::splitCriticalEdges\(BasicBlock\*\s+Src, BasicBlock\*\s+Dst\)\s*\{\s*[\s\S]*?)(\s*auto\s+NewBB\s*=\s*SplitCriticalEdge\(Src,\s*Dst,\s*Options\);\s*)'
m=re.search(pattern,s)
if not m:
    print("Could not find splitCriticalEdges body region", file=sys.stderr); sys.exit(1)
prefix=m.group(1)
call=m.group(2)
insert = r'''
  // Avoid splitting edges from or to blocks with IndirectBr terminators/predecessors.
  Instruction *TI = Src->getTerminator();
  if (isa<IndirectBrInst>(TI))
    return nullptr;
  for (auto *Pred : predecessors(Dst)) {
    if (isa<IndirectBrInst>(Pred->getTerminator()))
      return nullptr;
  }
'''
s = s.replace(call, insert + call)
if s==orig:
    print("No change made", file=sys.stderr); sys.exit(1)
with open(path,'w') as f: f.write(s)
print("Patched", path)
PY
&& submit-patch
```

